    <apex:pageBlock title="About Mobile Lead Form">
        <p>
         <img src="http://www.webidercrm.com/assets/img/web2lead.png" style="float:right;" />
         Mobile Lead Form application is a device agnostic Visual Force and jQuery Mobile based lead capture form for any mobile device. <br />
        It allows end user to submit lead information via any of their mobile devices. The responsive design formats the form in accordance to device size. <br />
        </p>
        <p>
        Mobile Lead Form is TOUCH enabled and will work with Salesforce.com Touch and Native app as well. It adhers to Salesforce security guidelines for authentication. <br />
        However, if you want your Mobile Lead Form to be accessible via World Wide Web (WWW) without authentication to allow anyone to submit the lead, Please see section below  
        on "How to Setup Lead Form As a Public Site". In addition, please watch 2 mins Demo video below. 
        </p> 
       
        <p><font color='RED'> Please make sure you have Web-T-Lead functionality turn on in your org, in order to have Mobile Lead Form working.</font> <br />
           Following are the steup to make sure Web-To-Lead is enabled! <br /><br />
           1. Click on the Top Right drop down where your name shows up and Click on Setup <br />
           2. Go to App Setup Section > Customize > Leads > Click Web-to-Lead <br />
           3. Make sure under "Web-to-Lead Settings" the check mark is CHECKED for "Web-to-Lead Enabled" <br />
           4. If it is NOT enabled then click on "Edit" <br />
           5. Check the "Web-to-Lead Enabled" check box <br />
           6. Select the default lead creator <br /> 
           7. Click Save <br />     
        </p>
       
