    <font color='brown'> Note: By using this method there will not be any authentication required and anyone with the link should be able to access the Mobile Lead Form and submit the lead to your Salesforce.com org. </font> <br />
        <h2>How To Setup your Mobile Lead Form Page as a Public Site </h2>
     <p><font color='blue'> Pre-Requisite: Please make sure you have Web-T-Lead functionality turn on in your org, in order to have Mobile Lead Form working. (See steps above) </font> <br />
           Following are the steup to make sure Mobile Lead Form is setup as public site! <br /><br />
           1. Click on the Top Right drop down where your name shows up and Click on Setup <br />
           2. Goto App Setup > Develop > Sites <br />
           3. Select your site domain, remember, you can't change it afterwards. <br />
           4. Click on 'New' <br />
           5. Create a new Site and fill the fields like label, name, description, <b>Must check the "Active" checkbox</b> use Active Site Home Page and Select <b>"Mobile Lead Form"</b> visual force page.  <br />
           6. Save the Setting and click on your site.com URL to access this site via public url <br />
           7. Make a NOTE of your site url, as you can either share that URL with your audience or give this to  your web team to forward your website lead page to this public Salesforce site <br />
           8. For example: We have http://www.kashifahmed.com/mobileleadform forward to "http://kashidemo-developer-edition.na12.force.com/mobileleadform" Salesforce.com public site <br />
           9. Enjoy! as you have successfully setup a public site for your new Mobile Lead Form to capture lead submission from your site. <br />
     </p>
